(53, 4, 'anne01', 'Golden Hour Serenity: A  Picnic Escape', 'Immerse yourself in the enchanting allure of cottagecore, where the warmth of golden hour invites you to a serene picnic escape. Amidst the gentle bubbles and nature&#39;s symphony, embrace the simple joys of life.', 'cottagecore', 'cg1.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(54, 4, 'anne01', 'Whispers of Serenity: Exploring the Delightful Harmonies of Cottagecore Bliss', 'In the enchanting world of cottagecore, there exists a realm where time seems to slow down, and nature&#39;s melodies take center stage. This idyllic image captures the essence of a pastoral symphony, where babbling brooks and blooming petals create a harmonious tapestry. Join us as we embark on a journey through the whimsical beauty of cottagecore, where tranquility and serenity intertwine with every whisper of nature.', 'cottagecore', 'cg2.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(55, 4, 'anne01', 'Enchanting Elegance: The Ballet of Pink Tulips on the Mirror-Like Lake', 'In the ethereal realm where nature meets artistry, a mesmerizing scene unfolds - a delicate ballet of pink tulips gracefully adorning the tranquil surface of a mirror-like lake. Each bloom, a stroke of nature&#39;s paintbrush, whispers tales of serenity and beauty as it reflects in the crystal waters below.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;As the gentle ripples caress the petals, a symphony of tranquility resonates through the air, inviting all who gaze upon this picturesque sight to immerse themselves in a moment of pure aesthetic bliss. The soft hues of pink dance harmoniously with the azure sky, creating a canvas of perfection that captures the essence of natural elegance.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;In this fleeting moment frozen in time, the pink tulips stand as ambassadors of grace and purity, their reflection a silent ode to the beauty that surrounds us. Let us pause, breathe in the serenity, and allow the enchanting allure of the pink tulips on the lake to remind us of the simple yet profound joys that nature graciously bestows upon us.', 'cottagecore', 'cg3.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(56, 2, 'querencia', 'My Serotonin Symphony', 'cheers to youth, thank you for reminding me that it&#39;s okay to stumble and not know what to do. thank you for reminding me that amidst the sadness and heartbreaks, life will serve happiness too. things can get better. i can be happy. it will be okay.', 'kpop', 'kpop1.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(57, 2, 'querencia', 'The Tranquil Guardian: Seventeen', 'life is indeed not a race to be won nor a mountain to be conquered, we are but beginners in the art of living. cheers to youth served as a reminder for us to go easy on ourselves, as this is also the first time we’re living. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;cheers to youth is for the people who are still struggling, people who are confused on what they want, people who keep on doubting themselves, people who have lots of questions left unanswered, people who wishes that there will be someone who will be there for them, and those people who want to be FOUND without actually asking for it.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;no matter how many times you fall, stand up.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Cheers to youth, Cheers to 𝒐𝒖𝒓 𝒚𝒐𝒖𝒕𝒉 ⭐️', 'kpop', 'kpop2.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(58, 2, 'querencia', 'Cheers to our youth', 'an introvert, someone who overworks himself, someone who constantly seeks academic validation, someone who thinks he’s helpless, and someone who sees the world a bit differently than most. all may be misfits, but is that such a bad thing? we all have a place in this damned world.', 'kpop', 'kpop3.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(59, 2, 'querencia', 'Furiosa: A mad max saga', 'This film follows Furiosa as a child (Alyla Brown) and then as a young adult (Anya Taylor-Joy). When she is taken from her home and witnesses the death of a loved one, she vows to exact her revenge and return home. This becomes difficult when her kidnapper and leader of a band of motorcycle riding rovers, Dr. Dementus (Chris Hemsworth), tries to overtake the Citadel. Left there, she rises among the ranks in silence to become an Imperator, and finds a way out.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;That way out is a violent, dirty, action packed jaunt through the sandy desert. As with Fury Road, the stunts and practical effects are insane and precise. Miller at the top of his game here.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Taylor-Joy and Hemsworth are perfectly cast. It’s obvious that Hemsworth really enjoyed bringing this often crazed villain to life. Rounding out the top cast is Tom Burke who plays Jack, ruggedly handsome partner in crime to Furiosa.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The world building far surpasses that of Fury Road and that is what makes Furiosa a stand out prequel. Honestly, I think it’s superior to its predecessor in many ways. Hemsworth is a stark contrast to Tom Hardy’s Max in Fury Road as the male lead, and it’s obvious the cast got along here. No bitter battles over acting methods that happened between Theron and Hardy in the previous film.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;And what happens to Dementus in the end is so brilliant that it’s one of the best revenge arcs I’ve seen in a while. Genius move, Miller.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Four and a half stars. See it on the biggest screen possible.', 'entertainment', 'en1.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(60, 2, 'querencia', 'The menu', 'I saw The Menu for this first time on Thursday night and cackled nearly non-stop. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The beautiful food and landscapes, clownishly archetypal characters, and potential mortal peril captured my attention initially—but what truly sets The Menu apart from lesser films is an unwavering commitment to the bit.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;In terms of the plot, I don’t want to spoil too much, but I will say that Ralph Fiennes’ Chef Slowik is completely dedicated to executing his plan for a perfect dinner suited precisely for his dozen guests—which is unsettled when one of his invitees brings a different date, Margot Mills (played by Anna Taylor-Joy), due to a recent break-up. The chef is so committed to his personalized menu concept that he is disturbed enough by Margot’s appearance to question her wildly inappropriately before he can allow dinner to proceed.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The Chef’s commitment to the bit (at the expense of all social expectations and norms) resonates through every frame of the film, supported by commitment to the bit in terms of its direction, cinematography, and cast choices. No choice in creating this film was made without intention and care. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;If you enjoy commitment to the bit taken to its logical and horrifying extremes, I strongly recommend The Menu. ', 'entertainment', 'en2.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(61, 2, 'querencia', 'The Fall Guy', 'The Fall Guys is a movie that knows what it is: a fun and entertaining popcorn flick. Ryan Gosling is incredibly charming and charismatic as the main character. Emily Blunt is also very lovable as the love interest. Their romance works because both Ryan and Emily have excellent chemistry. The rest of the supporting cast knew what movie they were making and gave a hammy performance that worked for the movie.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;What makes this movie stand out is how it is a love letter to stunt performers, with the plot centred around it. It helps that the action scenes are excellent! The movie does suffer from a weak script that has jokes that don&#39;t land. It feels like everyone is doing improv leading to weak dialogue scenes.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Nevertheless, this is an enjoyable movie and it succeeds in making me appreciate stunt performers even more!', 'entertainment', 'en3.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
