(75, 2, 'querencia', 'Makeup reco', 'Hi guys,&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;We all know I have a Charlotte Tilbury addiction and is it out of hand? Absolutely! But is that going to stop? No Way! After Christmas Charlotte had 40% off gift sets on her website and of course I used this as a excuse to top up my makeup collection and add some bits to it. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The first kit I picked up was The Secret To Supermodel Eyes Kit, £25.00. This kit is the perfect edition to my collection because it comes with a Mini Pillow Talk mascara in Super Black which I recently ran out of. When it comes to Pillow Talk mascara&#39;s I usually use the Dream Pop formula which is the burgundy brown shade but I needed a black mascara back in my collection. You also get a full size Brow Fix Sculpting Gel which I haven&#39;t tried before. I love using products like these in my brows because they are pretty thick so they need taming.  &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The second kit I picked up is something I get every year, it&#39;s the Charlotte Tilbury&#39;s Iconic Mini Lip Trio Kit, £29.00. I love collecting these trio sets every year because they are so easy to throw into your handbag so you save a little space. In this years set you get the shades Supermodel, Walk Of No Shame and Pillow Talk. I have never tried the shade Supermodel before and it is stunning! It is described as mid-toned muted nude-rose matte lipstick. Of course by now we know the shade Walk Of No Shame which is the iconic red and Pillow Talk which is a nude pink tone. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;These kit&#39;s are great gifts because you get a chance to try multiple products for a reasonable price so usually I buy them as gifts but this time I treated myself. So if you need any gift ideas head over to CharlotteTilbury.com and as always all products mentioned are linked above.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Lot&#39;s of love,&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Que x x ', 'shopping', 'sp2.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
(76, 2, 'querencia', 'Makeup reco part2', 'Hi guys,&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;If you&#39;ve been reading my blog for a while now you will know I adore By Beauty Bay eyeshadow palettes! They are some of the most beautifully pigmented palettes out there that are also incredibly affordable. Honestly anytime someone asks me to recommend a brand that has really pigmented shadow 9 times out of 10 I&#39;ll say Beauty Bay. That being said today I&#39;m going to be chatting to you about the palettes I got for Christmas. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Like I said I&#39;ve been a fan of this brand for a long time and usually I get the 16 pan eyeshadow palettes from By Beauty but I don&#39;t own a lot of their bigger palettes. Luckily for me I have a parent who pays attention to the makeup I love and picked me up a few of the 42 colour palettes. The first palette I opened was the By Beauty Bay Berries 42 Colour Palette, £25.00.  This palette is every persons dream who love wearing pink, red and purple tones. In these palettes you get a mix of matte and shimmer shades and honestly playing with these shades are so fun because they blend like a dream and genuinely wear really well. The last year or 2 I have really started loving a more vibrant eyeshadow look and this palette really fills in the gaps I had in my pink shadow collection. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The second palette I got was By Beauty Bay Midnight 42 Colour Palette, £25.00.  I have a mini version of this eyeshadow palette from the collection and it is by far my favourite colour story from this collection. I was so excited to open this palette because when it comes to vibrant shadows I usually go towards the blues and purples which this palette covers every version of those shades you could ever need. I also feel like this palette is the perfect partner to the Taylor Swift Midnight&#39;s album which is perfect since that&#39;s my eras outfit for June! Every time I pay with this palette I am always so excited to see what eye look I finish with. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;And lastly we have By Beauty Bay Earthy 42 Colour Palette, £25.00. When I opened this palette I was really excited because it&#39;s a gorgeous mix of warm tones,greens, golds, and browns. When you look at my palette collection overall I really don&#39;t own shades like this so I&#39;m really excited to use this palette and try out some more green / brown toned eye looks. I have already used the red and gold tones and they look stunning on the eyes. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Considering each of these palettes gives you 42 shades for £25 each, the palettes have gorgeous colour stories, are insanely pigmented and wear better then some high end brands I adore. So if you want to expand your shadow collections to more vibrant shades I really recommend checking out these palettes. As always all products mentioned are linked above.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Lot’s of love&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Que x x', 'shopping', 'sp3.jpg', '0000-00-00', 'active'),
